# Capital calls — the approval-pipeline vertical slice.
# Works with the VS Code REST Client, Visual Studio, and Rider .http support.
# Auth is the dev header scheme: X-User-Id = a seeded staff user id.
#   u-jchen (Ops Analyst, stage 1) · u-mreyes (Deal Lead, 2) · u-spatel (CIO, 3)
#   u-jokafor (Counsel, 4) · u-talvarez (Ops Manager, 5) · u-dwhitfield (Fund Accountant, 6)
#   u-pnair (Compliance, escalation sign-off) · u-admin (Administrator, full)

@host = http://localhost:8080
@user = u-jokafor

### Session user (drives approval affordances)
GET {{host}}/api/me
X-User-Id: {{user}}

### Blotter — all capital calls
GET {{host}}/api/capital-calls
X-User-Id: {{user}}

### Call detail — #C-2041 sits at Legal awaiting J. Okafor
GET {{host}}/api/capital-calls/call-2041
X-User-Id: {{user}}

### Workflow config (9 stages + escalation rules)
GET {{host}}/api/workflows/capital-calls
X-User-Id: {{user}}

### Needs-attention inbox (computed per caller via Dapper)
GET {{host}}/api/needs-attention
X-User-Id: {{user}}

### Create a call (wizard 2c) — allocations must reconcile to the amount
POST {{host}}/api/capital-calls
X-User-Id: u-jchen
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dealId": "deal-atlas",
  "amount": 12.30,
  "dueDate": "2026-07-20",
  "basis": "unfunded",
  "allocations": [
    { "investorId": "inv-redwood", "amount": 6.15 },
    { "investorId": "inv-blueharbor", "amount": 6.15 }
  ]
}

### Create a call > $20M — triggers the CIO + Compliance escalation
POST {{host}}/api/capital-calls
X-User-Id: u-jchen
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "dealId": "deal-atlas",
  "amount": 25.00,
  "dueDate": "2026-07-28",
  "basis": "unfunded",
  "allocations": [
    { "investorId": "inv-redwood", "amount": 10.00 },
    { "investorId": "inv-cascade", "amount": 15.00 }
  ]
}

### Approve the current stage (comment required; must be the stage's approver role)
POST {{host}}/api/capital-calls/call-2041/approve
X-User-Id: u-jokafor
Content-Type: application/json

{ "comment": "LPA §4.2 reviewed — clear to proceed" }

### Reject → returns the call to the prior stage as Returned
POST {{host}}/api/capital-calls/call-2041/reject
X-User-Id: u-jokafor
Content-Type: application/json

{ "comment": "Allocation for Cascade needs rework" }
